          <avActivityHighlights>Wind slabs and wet snow represent the main danger.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>In particular on steep slopes individual small to medium-sized slab avalanches are possible above approximately 1400 m. &lt;br/&gt; In the vicinity of peaks a dangerous avalanche situation will be encountered in some localities. The more recent wind slabs and can be released easily. &lt;br/&gt; Avalanches can penetrate down to the ground and reach medium size in some cases.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>The small quantity of fresh snow and in particular the wind slabs formed by the strong wind are lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack. &lt;br/&gt; The high temperatures from the late morning will give rise to increasing softening of the snowpack in some cases in particular on sunny slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
